snippet.textDisplay: I think his reputation and status as possible GOAT is forever tarnished. He tried to use his position to avoid the rule of law of a nation and a tournament he claims to love. He dragged the sport of tennis through the gutter in the last few weeks because of his own anti-vax beliefs and I for one am happy that Australia stood up to pressure and media by not flinching and recognising the sacrifices that their own citizens have withstood throughout what is a global pandemic. Australia demand double vaccination of anybody entering their country and this should and has to be respected as their sovereign right. It is true there were several misteps along the way but ultimately in my opinion this sets a very positive precedent that nobody is above the law of the land regardless of your status. Novak Djokovic is only a sports person after all, and I as a tennis fan feel its more important that the message to society and the younger generation has to be that vaccinations in a global pandemic is paramount. If Djokovic doesn't want to be vaxxed then don't but respect a society that does and if you choose to enter that country then get vaxxed or stay home. He made a drama of this whole situation, including his family riling up the anti-vax minority in Serbia and avoided questions on his movement whilst positive when going to events in Serbia. He has let himself down and has allowed his own arrogance to stain tennis unfortunately.
